dc_description_s: Wisconsin Department of Natural Resources1;24,000 scale hydrography (statewide) consists of a series of features including: (1) Natural bounding lines of hydro waterbody features; (2)Linear features representing streams, rivers and artificial flow through water; (3) Linear features representing streams, rivers and artificial flow through water that have been assigned a Waterbody Identification Code - WBIC; (4) Junction point features used to establish point attributes on a network; (5)Linear features including channel in water, original water course, fish hatchery walls, etc.; (6) Hydrological Point data such as springs, etc.; (7) Water features such as Lakes, Reservoirs, Wide Streams and River, and Unspecified Open Water features.; (8) Water features such as Lakes, Reservoirs, Wide Streams and River, and Unspecified Open Water features that have been assigned a Waterbody Identification Code - WBIC.
uw_supplemental_s: Augmented original metadata with UW-Madison specific elements. Individual REST Services are available for individual feature clases and are accessable from the following link: https://data-wi-dnr.opendata.arcgis.com/datasets?q=24k%20hydro
